  "title": "Compliance Officer/Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Ensure the fund management company operates in compliance with MAS regulations, fund-specific guidelines, and internal policies while supporting client onboarding and operational excellence.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Ensure compliance of fund management operations with MAS regulations, fund-specific guidelines, and internal policies to mitigate regulatory risks</li></ul><ul><li>Monitor and review fund operations, investment activities, and reporting procedures to maintain regulatory adherence and operational integrity</li></ul><ul><li>Support relationship managers by facilitating client onboarding, managing accounts, and delivering investor servicing to enhance client satisfaction</li></ul><ul><li>Maintain accurate and up-to-date client records and ensure timely, clear communication with clients to support relationship management</li></ul><ul><li>Collaborate with internal teams to promptly address client inquiries and resolve operational issues, ensuring seamless service delivery</li></ul><ul><li>Process invoices, reimbursements, and perform basic accounting tasks as needed to support financial operations</li></ul><ul><li>Execute ad-hoc administrative tasks efficiently to enhance overall team productivity and operational support</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>5 years of manager-level experience in a fund management company in Singapore (preferred, not a must)</li></ul>",
